Good morning, Carl,
On Thu, 21 Oct 1999 cspeare@us.ibm.com wrote:
> Don't know if this idea has been brought up before, but a lot of mailing lists
	From time to time...
> make a habit of putting the name of the list in brackets in the subject, as I
> have
> done. This is a cool thing because it allows people to easily set up scripts to
> filter their mail into folders. Having about 4 mailing list subscriptions I find
> it a
> valuable feature. Anyone else think this is a good idea?
	Having 61 mailing list subscriptions, I find procmail to be a
valuable feature :-).  Set up procmail to handle mail processing, then add
these lines to ~/.procmailrc :
:0:
* ^Sender:.*owner-linux-kernel@vger.rutgers.edu
linux-kernel
	Please bring any additional discussion to private mail. Cheers,
	- Bill
P.S.  Please don't CC: Linus - he's not repsonsible for the lists and gets
too much mail as it is.  List management is handled by Matti Aarnio
<matti.aarnio@sonera.fi> and friends...
